  "name": "Irresistible Demand",
  "permission": {
    "default": 0
  },
  "type": "feat",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>At 8th level, you can force others to do your bidding. As a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Standard-Actions\">standard action</a>, you attempt to dominate a creature as though using the @Compendium[pf1.spells.66s5qm8kwycgobce]{Dominate Monster}&nbsp;spell, except that the creature must have a number of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/glossary#TOC-Hit-Dice-HD-\">Hit Dice</a>&nbsp;equal to or less than your wizard level. The targeted creature receives a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Will\">Will</a>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Saving-Throws\">saving throw</a>&nbsp;each round to negate the effect. The DC is equal to 10 + 1/2 your wizard level + your&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Intelligence-Int-\">Intelligence</a>&nbsp;modifier. You can dominate creatures for a number of rounds per day equal to your wizard level. These rounds do not need to be consecutive. You must concentrate as a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Standard-Actions\">standard action</a>&nbsp;to maintain control over a dominated creature.</p>",
